Cleveland Cavaliers star LeBron James has said he will be honoured to play in front of Prince William and Kate Middleton.

The royal couple will attend the Cavaliers game with the Brooklyn Nets at the Barclays Center on Monday night, and even James appeared star-struck. 

'It's a huge honour,' the 29-year-old told reporters. 'The stuff that you read about, people like them are only in books growing up. 

